parameters.content:
## Sort and Delete rows
A sort node is used delete from descending order rather than ascending. This makes sure the delete row node always deletes tickets from the bottom-up, preventing index shifts from ruining the mapping.

If any tickets found in the sheet that are not in the API, get removed from the sheet.

## Login credentials
Workflow is scheduled to run every 5 mins.

An HTTP Login node is used to proof the user is an admin of SysAid using SysAid's api.


A set node is used to get the ID from the header of the user, extracted and saved to use later to retrieve info from SysAid.

## Get Ticket's that are open

HTTP node to grab all the status'. 

Set node to grab the relevant status' that are deemed "Open".

HTTP node to grab tickets that have the status that are open.

Grab all fields from the Api Ticket HTTP node.

## Append and Read

Tickets are appended in the google sheet followed by a Read sheet node.

The read sheet node returns row number and is set using a set node. This will help determine which rows from the sheet are not drawn from the api for deletion.

## Merge and Compare

A simple merge node that merges the info from the API and the info from the google sheet.

The code node then does a comparison using info from the merge node. If a ticket that's in the sheet is not found from the Api, it gets marked for deletion.
